vers the strategies implemented by American mathematicians in their quest for the advancement of knowledge. Throughout, she considers how geopolitical circumstances shifted the course of the discipline.Examining how the American mathematical community asserted itself on the international stage, The New Era in American Mathematics, 1920-1950 shows the ways one nation became the focal point for the field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMathematicsxResearchzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aMATHEMATICS / History & Philosophy.2bisacsh  aAcademia Sinica.  aActa Arithmetica.  aAftermath of World War II.  aAmerican Association of Physics Teachers.  aAmerican Council on Education.  aAmerican Institute of Physics.  aAmerican Journal of Mathematics.  aAmerican Mathematical Monthly.  aAmerican Mathematical Society.  aAmerican Statistical Association.  aAnalytic continuation.  aAnnals of Mathematical Statistics.  aAnnals of Mathematics.  aAnnals of Science.  aApplied mathematics.  aBulletin of the American Mathematical Society.  aChancellor (education).  aCharacterization (mathematics).  aComplex number.  aConnecticut College.  aDivision algebra.  aDuke Mathematical Journal.  aEdward R. Murrow.  aEstimation theory.  aEuclidean space.  aEuropean Mathematical Society.  aFourier series.  aFundamenta Mathematicae.  aGeorg Cantor.  aHilbert's fifth problem.  aHyperbolic partial differential equation.  aIdeal (ring theory).  aInternational Congress of Mathematicians.  aIntersection theory.  aIntroduction to general relativity.  aJohn von Neumann.  aJoint Policy Board for Mathematics.  aLondon Mathematical Society.  aMathematical Association of America.  aMathematical physics.  aMathematical table.  aMathematician.  aMathematics.  aMethoden